 and asking that this be orthogonal to 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{2}$
\end_inset

 implies that 
\begin_inset Formula $c=d=0$
\end_inset

 so that 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{4}=\left(0,0,a-1,1,0,\cdots\right)$
\end_inset

.
