 and asking for orthgonality to 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{1}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{2}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{3}$
\end_inset

 means 
\begin_inset Formula $a=b=c=0$
\end_inset

 so that 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{6}=\left(0,0,0,-1,0,1,0,\cdots\right)$
\end_inset

.
